                        <div class="d-block p-5 text-center  bg-white border">
                            <strong class="d-block h4 mb-2">Auto Upgrades</strong>
                            <span class="d-block mb-0">
                                Plato offers automated detection and upgrading of out of date modules.
                            </span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                        <div class="d-block p-5 text-center bg-white border">
                            <strong class="d-block h4 mb-2">
                                Events & Messages
                            </strong>
                            <span class="d-block mb-0">
                                Modules can hook into hundreds of events exposed via the Plato message broker.
                            </span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                        <div class="d-block p-5 text-center bg-white border">
                            <strong class="d-block h4 mb-2">Interfaces</strong>
                            <span class="d-block mb-0">
                                Plato exposes hundreds of interfaces developers can implement to extend Plato.
                            </span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                        <div class="d-block p-5 text-center bg-white border">
                            <strong class="d-block h4 mb-2">Versioning</strong>
                            <span class="d-block mb-0">
                                As modules are versioned they can be released independently of the Plato core.
                            </span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- An Extensible Modular Architecture -->
<section class="page bg-primary-25">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="p-5 bg-white">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-12 text-center text-lg-left ">
                    <img alt="Plato Logo" src="~/plato.site/content/images/vsmodules.png" class="img-md-fluid float-none float-lg-right mx-md-auto max-w-500 d-inline-block ml-lg-5 mb-4 mb-lg-0" />
                    <h1 class="font-weight-bold text-primary text-uppercase">
                        An Extensible Modular Architecture
                    </h1>
                    <p class="mt-4">
                        Plato is built from the ground up to be highly extensible via the built-in module system.
                        All features offered by Plato are built upon this same module system.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Modules are independent NuGet packages or Visual Studio projects that can extend Plato to add or modify functionality. Plato exposes hundreds of extensibility points allowing module developers to easily customize any aspect of Plato.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        You can see various module projects provided with Plato opposite within the Visual Studio solution explorer.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <h3 class="font-weight-light">
                            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg my-4" href="https://github.com/InstantASP/plato/tree/master/src/Plato/Modules" target="_blank">
                                <img src="~/plato.site/content/images/octocat-icon-light.png" alt="GitHub Octocat Logo" title="GitHub Octocat Logo" class="max-w-40 align-middle mr-2" />Browse all modules on GitHub...
                            </a>
                        </h3>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Call to action -->
<section class="page bg-primary">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-12 text-center">
                <h1 class="text-uppercase font-weight-bold text-white">
